===球員===
A native of [[Kingswood,_South_Gloucestershire|Kingswood]], [[Bristol|Bristol]], Holloway grew up in [[Cadbury_Heath|Cadbury Heath]], where his mother Jean still lives in the same council house. Holloway went to Sir Bernard Lovell School in Oldland Common at the same time that [[Gary_Penrice|Gary Penrice]] was at Chase School for Boys in Mangotsfield.  They still remain close friends today. His father Bill – an amateur footballer – worked as a seaman and a factory worker. Holloway began his playing career as an apprentice with his hometown team [[Bristol_Rovers_F.C.|Bristol Rovers]], turning professional in March 1981 and making his league debut the same year. He usually played on the right side of midfield, and made his name as one of the more promising players in the [[Football_League_Third_Division|Third Division]] (now [[Football_League_One|League One]]). After four seasons at Rovers, he was transferred to [[Wimbledon_F.C.|Wimbledon]] in July 1985 for £35,000.

His stay at Wimbledon was a short one. In March 1986, after less than one year at the club, he was sold to [[Brentford_F.C.|Brentford]] for £25,000, where he also spent just a little over a year. In January 1987 he joined [[Torquay_United_F.C.|Torquay United]] on loan, playing 5 times. In August 1987, after two disappointing years in [[London|London]], Holloway returned to Bristol Rovers for a fee of £10,000.

Back at Rovers, who were now playing "home" games at [[Twerton_Park|Twerton Park]] in [[Bath,_Somerset|Bath]], and under the wing of new Rovers manager [[Gerry_Francis|Gerry Francis]], Holloway flourished. In four seasons, he missed only five games. When Francis was appointed manager of [[Football_League_First_Division|First Division]] side [[Queens_Park_Rangers_F.C.|QPR]] in 1991, one of his first signings was Holloway, for a fee of £230,000 in August 1991. Holloway spent five seasons at QPR, playing more than 150 games for the club, before returning to Bristol Rovers for the third time in August 1996, this time as player-manager.
