On 21 May 2009 it was reported that Holloway, after 363 days out of football, was set to be announced as the new manager of Blackpool following the departure of their [[caretaker_manager|caretaker manager]] [[Tony_Parkes|Tony Parkes]]. The appointment was confirmed later the same day with Holloway signing a one-year contract with the club.<ref name="Blackpool unveil Holloway">{{Cite news| title=Blackpool unveil Holloway| url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/b/blackpool/8061441.stm | publisher= [[bbc.co.uk|bbc.co.uk]]| date=21 May 2009| accessdate=21 May 2009}}</ref> His first league game in charge of ''the Seasiders'' was a 1–1 draw with his former club Queens Park Rangers at [[Loftus_Road|Loftus Road]] on 8 August 2009, the opening day of the [[Blackpool_F.C._season_2009-10|2009–10]] season.

